Transforming Data

Notes: Engagement variables with higher magnitude of data. Transform the data by using log or square root. May be turn into normal distribution or known distribution.

Add a Scaling Layer

Notes: To avoid log of zero, add one to values before applying log. http://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/scale_continuous.html

ggplot(data = pf, aes(x = friend_count)) + 
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 50, color = 'black', fill = 'light blue') + 
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0,1000), breaks = seq(0, 1000, 100)) + 
  labs( title = 'Friend Count without Transformation')
## Warning: Removed 2951 rows containing non-finite values (stat_bin).

ggplot(data = pf, aes(x = friend_count )) + 
  geom_histogram( color = 'black', fill = 'light blue') + 
  scale_x_log10() + 
  labs(title = 'Friend Count with Log Transformation')
## Warning: Transformation introduced infinite values in continuous x-axis
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.
## Warning: Removed 1962 rows containing non-finite values (stat_bin).

ggplot(data = pf, aes(x = friend_count )) + 
  geom_histogram( color = 'black', fill = 'light blue') + 
  scale_x_sqrt() + 
  labs(title = 'Friend Count with Log Transformation')
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

###All independent plot in one canvas
#install.packages("gridExtra", dependencies = T)
library(gridExtra)
p1 = ggplot(data = pf, aes(x = friend_count)) + 
  geom_histogram( color = 'black', fill = 'light blue') +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0,1000))
p2 = ggplot(data = pf, aes(x = log10(friend_count + 1))) + 
  geom_histogram( color = 'black', fill = 'yellow')
p3 = ggplot(data = pf, aes(x = sqrt(friend_count))) + 
  geom_histogram( color = 'black', fill = 'light green') +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0,40))
grid.arrange(p1, p2, p3, ncol = 1)

Frequency Polygons

ggplot(aes(x = friend_count, y = ..count../sum(..count..)),
  data = subset(pf, !is.na(gender))) +
  geom_freqpoly(aes(color = gender), binwidth=10) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 1000), breaks = seq(0, 1000, 50)) +
  xlab('Friend Count') +
  ylab('Proportion of users with that friend count')

Getting Logical

pf$check_in <- ifelse(pf$likes > 0, 1, 0)
pf$check_in <- factor(pf$check_in)
pf$mobile_check_in <- ifelse(pf$mobile_likes > 0, 1, 0)
